  "name": "Hall Sensor Polarity Demo",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Hall Sensor Polarity Demo",
    "description": "Same circuit as lesson 50 (USB → 470Ω → SIG T → LED; east column 10kΩ pull-up to the Hall at 0°). No new wiring — the lesson is what you do with the magnet. With no magnet nearby the pull-up holds SIG high and the LED stays off; bring a pole close and the LED snaps on when SIG pulls low. Flip the magnet (N vs S toward the sensor) or approach from different sides: one pole may turn the LED on, the other off, or you may see little change until you are close. Compare lesson 50 (trigger behavior) and lesson 49 (detection). Hall at 0°; LED at 90°."
  },
